Start with the template architecture, not the generator script.

Your current Python generator already supports Jinja includes from /templates, so we can reorganize templates/partials/ and templates/ks/ without changing Python yet. The _meta.yml files will be ignored by the generator for now, but they will set us up for the future custom override builder.

Start here

Do this in this order:

1. Create the new numbered partial directory layout.
2. Add _meta.yml files to each partial slot.
3. Create only the minimal/common partials first.
4. Rebuild rhel8-minimal.ks.j2, rhel9-minimal.ks.j2, and rhel10-minimal.ks.j2 using the new partial paths.
5. Run the image tests.
6. Then move on to small-disk.
7. Then move on to developer-workstation.

Do not start with developer workstation. That one has the most site-specific and risky stuff, so it should be last.

