_meta.yml fields I would use

Keep it simple, but useful enough for the future helper script:

title: Install mode
required: true
selection: one
default: graphical.ks.j2
description: Choose whether Anaconda runs in text mode or graphical mode.

I would use these fields:

title: Human-readable section name
required: true
selection: one
default: file-name.ks.j2
description: Short explanation for non-Linux users.
applies_to:
  os:
    - rhel7
    - rhel8
    - rhel9
    - rhel10
  profiles:
    - minimal
    - small_disk
    - developer_workstation

The most important field is selection.

Use:

selection: one

when the user should pick exactly one option, like text vs graphical.

Use:

selection: many

when multiple options can be included from that slot.

Use:

selection: optional

when the whole section can be skipped.

Use:

selection: fixed

when the section should normally always be included and the user should not be prompted unless they are doing advanced customization.

Examples:

title: EULA
required: true
selection: fixed
default: agreed.ks.j2
description: Adds the required Red Hat license agreement line.
title: Install mode
required: true
selection: one
default: graphical.ks.j2
description: Choose whether the installer uses text mode or graphical mode.
title: Post-install actions
required: false
selection: one
default: empty.ks.j2
description: Optional commands to run after installation.

